summary: Talking Detective Pikachu with Detective Pikachu! (Kaiji Tang) - Kirblog 12/1/18 It's time yet again for Pokecember! While I'm...
caption:
Talking Detective Pikachu with Detective Pikachu! (Kaiji Tang) - Kirblog 12/1/18

It’s time yet again for Pokecember! While I’m off today seeing Pokemon’s 21st Animated Movie, the thing on everyone’s minds lately is the trailer for the upcoming “Detective Pikachu” movie! So, to discuss the film and the entire existence of a talking Pikachu with a grizzled grumpy voice, I’m joined by Kaiji Tang, voice of the Detective himself! The advent of a live-action Pokemon movie has been a fantasy for many fans for 20 years and with it finally on the horizon, there’s a lot to take in. Hope you enjoy our thoughts and be sure to leave yours in the comments below!

Follow Kaiji Tang on social media! Hear his voice in the Detective Pikachu video game for Nintendo 3DS!
https://twitter.com/KaijiTang

summary: Another thing I’d like to see is Detective Pikachu straight up... Kill something. Like, Detective Pikachu being beaten the shit...
body:
Another thing I’d like to see is Detective Pikachu straight up… Kill something. Like, Detective Pikachu being beaten the shit out of them and managing to to nothing but then the Kid is about to die and the villain taunts the rodent so Detective Pikachu goes “No one mess with my friend!” or something and with the power of friendship he fucking… kills someone.

He overcharges and in a fit of rage thundershocks the villain to death. For his friend.

Because we all know that’s something OG Pikachu would have done too had he been in a gritty noir movie rather than a children cartoon.

title: Daily Doodles
body:
I am still getting used to Manga Studio’s brushes. I might play around with Illustrator this evening. Still, this came out pretty fun. I can’t wait to have more free time this weekend. :3 😀

Success! I made the line art look much better than this morning’s attempt. Who knew zooming in would be so helpful. XD (I have much to learn about digital inking. It is nice to have tutorials.)

On a less than stellar note, my tablet computer shut off in the middle of me trying to color this, so I am pretty annoyed by that. I might have to reset Windows and reinstall everything. That is annoying. We shall see.
